    },
    {
      "id": 99,
      "start": 225.04,
      "end": 226.64,
      "text": "And then going forward,"
    },
    {
      "id": 100,
      "start": 226.64,
      "end": 228.0,
      "text": "when I put it all together,"
    },
    {
      "id": 101,
      "start": 228.96,
      "end": 231.12,
      "text": "here, then as I do my,"
    },
    {
      "id": 102,
      "start": 231.12,
      "end": 233.96,
      "text": "select ER3 level,"
    },
    {
      "id": 103,
      "start": 233.96,
      "end": 235.92,
      "text": "well, that's just whatever came out of this one."
    },
    {
      "id": 104,
      "start": 241.76,
      "end": 242.6,
      "text": "Okay."
    },
    {
      "id": 105,
      "start": 245.2,
      "end": 248.68,
      "text": "So now, if you throw this to the query out in the SQL server,"
    },
    {
      "id": 106,
      "start": 248.68,
      "end": 251.44,
      "text": "what you end up with is all this cross-applies,"
    },
    {
      "id": 107,
      "start": 251.44,
      "end": 256.44,
      "text": "get turned out and simplified into just a left out or join."
    },
    {
      "id": 108,
      "start": 258.16,
      "end": 261.6,
      "text": "Against the, against the order table."
    },
    {
      "id": 109,
      "start": 261.6,
      "end": 262.44,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 110,
      "start": 262.44,
      "end": 266.6,
      "text": "So you're looping every single customer record."
    },
    {
      "id": 111,
      "start": 266.6,
      "end": 270.76,
      "text": "And then you do a left out or join to compute the maximum number"
    },
    {
      "id": 112,
      "start": 270.76,
      "end": 274.92,
      "text": "of, or the total amount of items that they bought."
    },
    {
      "id": 113,
      "start": 274.92,
      "end": 276.36,
      "text": "If they don't have them bought anything,"
    },
    {
      "id": 114,
      "start": 276.36,
      "end": 278.08,
      "text": "you get null, that's fine."
    },
    {
      "id": 115,
      "start": 279.24,
      "end": 281.84,
      "text": "Otherwise, you didn't compute what the true output is."
    },
    {
      "id": 116,
      "start": 286.08,
      "end": 286.92,
      "text": "Pretty cool."
    },
    {
      "id": 117,
      "start": 289.0,
      "end": 290.72,
      "text": "Again, I'll say this next week,"
    },
    {
      "id": 118,
      "start": 290.72,
      "end": 294.0,
      "text": "for most things, SQL server will have the best query optimizer"
    },
    {
      "id": 119,
      "start": 295.0,
      "end": 295.84,
      "text": "in the world."
    },
    {
      "id": 120,
      "start": 296.92,
      "end": 299.72,
      "text": "Not for some things, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 121,
      "start": 299.72,
      "end": 301.68,
      "text": "For joins, for next queries,"
    },
    {
      "id": 122,
      "start": 301.68,
      "end": 304.32,
      "text": "the umbral hyper one will be better."
    },
    {
      "id": 123,
      "start": 304.32,
      "end": 305.48,
      "text": "And Dr. B's getting there."
    },
    {
      "id": 124,
      "start": 307.36,
      "end": 309.88,
      "text": "Well, I'll talk, I'll give a preview"
    },
    {
      "id": 125,
      "start": 309.88,
      "end": 311.0,
      "text": "of what we'll talk about next week"
    },
    {
      "id": 126,
      "start": 311.0,
      "end": 312.76,
      "text": "at the end of this class tonight, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 127,
      "start": 312.76,
      "end": 316.08,
      "text": "So in this case, here, now, what do we have, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 128,
      "start": 316.08,
      "end": 320.8,
      "text": "We, there was an implicit join in our UDF"
    },
    {
      "id": 129,
      "start": 320.8,
      "end": 325.12,
      "text": "that because we converted it into this cross-supply,"
    },
    {
      "id": 130,
      "start": 325.12,
      "end": 329.92,
      "text": "this lateral join contraption here,"
    },
    {
      "id": 131,
      "start": 329.92,
      "end": 332.04,
      "text": "that the query optimizer was able to figure,"
    },
    {
      "id": 132,
      "start": 332.04,
      "end": 336.48,
      "text": "oh, it's actually, it is a join against the,"
    },
    {
      "id": 133,
      "start": 336.48,
      "end": 338.0,
      "text": "between the orders and customer table."
    },
    {
      "id": 134,
      "start": 338.0,
      "end": 339.4,
      "text": "And in particular, it's a left out or join,"
    },
    {
      "id": 135,
      "start": 339.4,
      "end": 342.88,
      "text": "because I may not always have an order record for a customer."
    },
    {
      "id": 136,
      "start": 342.88,
      "end": 346.08,
      "text": "And so now I can just in line or, you know,"
    },
    {
      "id": 137,
      "start": 346.08,
      "end": 347.4,
      "text": "do a join as I normally would,"
    },
    {
      "id": 138,
      "start": 347.4,
      "end": 349.04,
      "text": "do the hash join really quickly,"
    },
    {
      "id": 139,
      "start": 349.04,
      "end": 350.72,
      "text": "but we know how to do."
    },
    {
      "id": 140,
      "start": 350.72,
      "end": 353.88,
      "text": "All of the operations that were previously a black box"
    },
    {
      "id": 141,
      "start": 353.88,
      "end": 356.96,
      "text": "inside of our UDF are now embedded as SQL"
    },
    {
      "id": 142,
      "start": 356.96,
      "end": 358.8,
      "text": "in the query optimizer can use all the statistics"
    },
    {
      "id": 143,
      "start": 358.8,
      "end": 360.28,
      "text": "and other information that it has"
    },
    {
      "id": 144,
      "start": 360.28,
      "end": 362.44,
      "text": "to be able to reason about the selectivity estimates"
    },
    {
      "id": 145,
      "start": 362.44,
      "end": 364.48,
      "text": "for our query."
    },
    {
      "id": 146,
      "start": 364.48,
      "end": 367.64,
      "text": "It's paralyzeable now, because we know there's nothing,"
    },
    {
      "id": 147,
      "start": 367.64,
      "end": 369.68,
      "text": "there's no weird dependencies between, you know,"
    },
    {
      "id": 148,
      "start": 369.68,
      "end": 372.16,
      "text": "evoking this function, or sorry, this query,"
    },
    {
      "id": 149,
      "start": 372.16,
      "end": 373.8,
      "text": "from one record to the next."
    },
    {
      "id": 150,
      "start": 373.8,
      "end": 375.48,
      "text": "So all my threads can be running this,"
    },
    {
      "id": 151,
      "start": 375.48,
      "end": 377.84,
      "text": "and parallel at the same time."
    },
    {
      "id": 152,
      "start": 377.84,
      "end": 380.12,
      "text": "There's no function call overhead of, you know,"
    },
    {
      "id": 153,
      "start": 380.12,
      "end": 382.32,
      "text": "setting up the call stack to go into some function"
    },
    {
      "id": 154,
      "start": 382.32,
      "end": 384.16,
      "text": "for every single record."
    },
    {
      "id": 155,
      "start": 384.16,
      "end": 386.16,
      "text": "And furthermore, though, they claim that in the,"
    },
    {
      "id": 156,
      "start": 386.16,
      "end": 387.96,
      "text": "in the Freud paper, one of the big advantages"
    },
    {
      "id": 157,
      "start": 387.96,
      "end": 390.6,
      "text": "of their approaches didn't require any engineering changes"
    },
    {
      "id": 158,
      "start": 390.6,
      "end": 393.48,
      "text": "or changes to the query optimizer itself."
    },
    {
      "id": 159,
      "start": 393.48,
      "end": 395.92,
      "text": "Because that's a whole complicated piece of a machinery"
    },
    {
      "id": 160,
      "start": 395.92,
      "end": 397.36,
      "text": "inside the data server."
    },
    {
      "id": 161,
      "start": 397.36,
      "end": 399.88,
      "text": "And then if you can avoid having to modify that,"
    },
    {
      "id": 162,
      "start": 399.88,
      "end": 401.64,
      "text": "and therefore you know there won't be any regressions"
    },
    {
      "id": 163,
      "start": 401.64,
      "end": 405.68,
      "text": "for anybody else, then this is fantastic."
    },
    {
      "id": 164,
      "start": 409.4,
      "end": 412.36,
      "text": "So if your query optimizer is very sophisticated,"
    },
    {
      "id": 165,
      "start": 412.36,
      "end": 415.24,
      "text": "in the case of SQL Server 1 is, you actually get a lot"
    },
    {
      "id": 166,
      "start": 415.24,
      "end": 416.52,
      "text": "of the same optimization advantages."
    },
    {
      "id": 167,
      "start": 416.52,
      "end": 417.76,
      "text": "You would get in a, what I'll call,"
    },
    {
      "id": 168,
      "start": 417.76,
      "end": 421.04,
      "text": "traditional optimizer, or compiler,"
    },
    {
      "id": 169,
      "start": 421.04,
      "end": 424.0,
      "text": "optimizing compiler, like for Clang or GCC."
    },
    {
      "id": 170,
      "start": 424.0,
      "end": 426.0,
      "text": "You basically get the same benefits"
    },
    {
      "id": 171,
      "start": 426.0,
      "end": 428.56,
      "text": "in now inside your UDF."
    },
    {
      "id": 172,
      "start": 428.56,
      "end": 430.96,
      "text": "So let's say I have a really simple UDF,"
    },
    {
      "id": 173,
      "start": 430.96,
      "end": 433.64,
      "text": "giving some integer, and I return back whether it's a high value,"
    },
    {
      "id": 174,
      "start": 433.64,
      "end": 435.44,
      "text": "the string high value or low value."
    },
    {
      "id": 175,
      "start": 435.44,
      "end": 436.84,
      "text": "So I would invoke it as, you know,"
    },
    {
      "id": 176,
      "start": 436.84,
      "end": 440.32,
      "text": "select get value as a passing in some kind of constant here."
    },
    {
      "id": 177,
      "start": 440.32,
      "end": 441.88,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 178,
      "start": 441.88,
      "end": 444.04,
      "text": "So if I Freud, Freud this mofo, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 179,
      "start": 444.04,
      "end": 446.72,
      "text": "I'm going to get, at least in the first version, something like this."
    },
    {
      "id": 180,
      "start": 446.72,
      "end": 449.92,
      "text": "We have the case when statement, if the value is greater than 1,000,"
    },
    {
      "id": 181,
      "start": 449.92,
      "end": 452.72,
      "text": "set up high, otherwise give it low."
    },
    {
      "id": 182,
      "start": 452.72,
      "end": 454.48,
      "text": "And then we do an outer apply."
    },
    {
      "id": 183,
      "start": 454.48,
      "end": 456.52,
      "text": "We can know what that is on that."
    },
    {
      "id": 184,
      "start": 456.52,
      "end": 458.72,
      "text": "And we get, you know, we return back"
    },
    {
      "id": 185,
      "start": 458.72,
      "end": 460.96,
      "text": "to the string high value or low value."
    },
    {
      "id": 186,
      "start": 460.96,
      "end": 466.04,
      "text": "Well, in a query optimizer, sorry, a traditional optimizer,"
    },
    {
      "id": 187,
      "start": 466.04,
      "end": 468.76,
      "text": "it would be to recognize that because I'm invoking this"
    },
    {
      "id": 188,
      "start": 468.76,
      "end": 472.64,
      "text": "with a constant value of, what was it, 5,000?"
    },
    {
      "id": 189,
      "start": 472.64,
      "end": 473.16,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 190,
      "start": 473.16,
      "end": 474.36,
      "text": "Yeah, 5,000."
    },
    {
      "id": 191,
      "start": 474.36,
      "end": 477.16,
      "text": "That I can do dynamic slicing and identify"
    },
    {
      "id": 192,
      "start": 477.16,
      "end": 481.56,
      "text": "that I'm never going to go down the, the else clause for low value."
    },
    {
      "id": 193,
      "start": 481.56,
      "end": 484.2,
      "text": "And I just remove that dead code entirely."
    },
    {
      "id": 194,
      "start": 484.2,
      "end": 485.28,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 195,
      "start": 485.28,
      "end": 487.72,
      "text": "In the case of the SQL query, it's the same thing as,"
    },
    {
      "id": 196,
      "start": 487.72,
      "end": 491.24,
      "text": "I've removed my case when, and I just have, you know,"
    },
    {
      "id": 197,
      "start": 491.24,
      "end": 495.84,
      "text": "just spit out the constant value high."
    },
    {
      "id": 198,
      "start": 495.84,
      "end": 498.48,
      "text": "Then, furthermore, I can do constant propagation and folding."
    },
    {
      "id": 199,
      "start": 498.48,
      "end": 500.96,
      "text": "Again, a traditional compiler optimizer would recognize"
    },
    {
      "id": 200,
      "start": 500.96,
      "end": 505.92,
      "text": "that, well, I don't need to concatenate high and value"
    },
    {
      "id": 201,
      "start": 505.92,
      "end": 507.44,
      "text": "as separate steps."
    },
    {
      "id": 202,
      "start": 507.44,
      "end": 509.88,
      "text": "I can just put them two together at the very beginning"
    },
    {
      "id": 203,
      "start": 509.88,
      "end": 511.84,
      "text": "by propagating the constant up."
    },
    {
      "id": 204,
      "start": 511.84,
      "end": 515.68,
      "text": "Same thing in our SQL query, the query optimizer could figure out,"
    },
    {
      "id": 205,
      "start": 515.84,
      "end": 518.4,
      "text": "well, this is just taking high, appending it to the string"
    },
    {
      "id": 206,
      "start": 518.4,
      "end": 519.48,
      "text": "vowel."
    },
    {
      "id": 207,
      "start": 519.48,
      "end": 523.68,
      "text": "So why do that as an out-on-apply with separate SQL queries?"
    },
    {
      "id": 208,
      "start": 523.68,
      "end": 528.08,
      "text": "Let me just do it in one statement."
    },
    {
      "id": 209,
      "start": 528.08,
      "end": 529.76,
      "text": "Even further, you do more dead code elimination,"
    },
    {
      "id": 210,
      "start": 529.76,
      "end": 533.88,
      "text": "saying, well, I don't need to declare an out-of-query return"
    },
    {
      "id": 211,
      "start": 533.88,
      "end": 536.84,
      "text": "value or setting up the variable and then turning it."
    },
    {
      "id": 212,
      "start": 536.84,
      "end": 538.04,
      "text": "It's just select high value."
    },
    {
      "id": 213,
      "start": 541.56,
      "end": 543.4,
      "text": "So again, you get all the same benefits"
    },
    {
      "id": 214,
      "start": 543.48,
      "end": 545.72,
      "text": "as if it was a traditional optimizer,"
    },
    {
      "id": 215,
      "start": 545.72,
      "end": 546.96,
      "text": "but the query optimizer is doing this,"
    },
    {
      "id": 216,
      "start": 546.96,
      "end": 549.64,
      "text": "because it already can do this for queries today."
    },
    {
      "id": 217,
      "start": 549.64,
      "end": 551.16,
      "text": "SQL server can, not everyone can."
    },
    {
      "id": 218,
      "start": 553.88,
      "end": 555.6,
      "text": "I don't think Postgres can do this."
    },
    {
      "id": 219,
      "start": 558.96,
      "end": 559.8,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 220,
      "start": 559.8,
      "end": 560.64,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 221,
      "start": 560.64,
      "end": 563.4,
      "text": "So if this works so well, can you just stop teaching people"
    },
    {
      "id": 222,
      "start": 563.4,
      "end": 565.28,
      "text": "see full and use PDFs?"
    },
    {
      "id": 223,
      "start": 565.28,
      "end": 566.76,
      "text": "Stabbing is, if this works so well,"
    },
    {
      "id": 224,
      "start": 566.76,
      "end": 569.44,
      "text": "can we just stop teaching people SQL and use"
    },
    {
      "id": 225,
      "start": 569.44,
      "end": 570.44,
      "text": "you desks or everything?"
    },
    {
      "id": 226,
      "start": 570.44,
      "end": 572.56,
      "text": "So again, it doesn't support everything."
    },
    {
      "id": 227,
      "start": 572.56,
      "end": 574.76,
      "text": "So as in 2019, this is what you can do."
    },
    {
      "id": 228,
      "start": 574.76,
      "end": 576.32,
      "text": "You can do clairs and sets."
    },
    {
      "id": 229,
      "start": 576.32,
      "end": 577.68,
      "text": "You have select queries."
    },
    {
      "id": 230,
      "start": 577.68,
      "end": 582.44,
      "text": "If then else, or if else, else if, if return clause"
    },
    {
      "id": 231,
      "start": 582.44,
      "end": 584.92,
      "text": "in multiple locations of the function,"
    },
    {
      "id": 232,
      "start": 584.92,
      "end": 587.52,
      "text": "which they can handle that, and they"
    },
    {
      "id": 233,
      "start": 587.52,
      "end": 590.16,
      "text": "do all basic relational operators, out of operators,"
    },
    {
      "id": 234,
      "start": 590.16,
      "end": 595.32,
      "text": "exist, not exist, is null in any and so forth."
    },
    {
      "id": 235,
      "start": 595.32,
      "end": 597.08,
      "text": "They don't support exceptions."
    },
    {
      "id": 236,
      "start": 597.08,
      "end": 598.48,
      "text": "They don't support dynamic SQL queries,"
    },
    {
      "id": 237,
      "start": 598.48,
      "end": 600.2,
      "text": "and they don't support updates."
    },
    {
      "id": 238,
      "start": 600.2,
      "end": 601.04,
      "text": "Again, in SQL."
    }
  ],
  "language": "en"
}